title: High-school graduates face worse prospects today than 20 years ago
text: Young people who enter the workforce with just their diploma face challenges, despite the low unemployment rate.

title: Stocks Advance Before Jobs Report As Dollar Gains: Markets Wrap
text: Stocks rose in Europe on Friday and U.S. equity futures edged higher in the run-up to a key American jobs report. The dollar climbed and Treasury yields ticked up.

title: Swiss Re presses ahead with flotation of $4.5 billion British unit
text: Swiss Re is pressing ahead with a flotation of British subsidiary ReAssure on the London Stock Exchange, the world's second largest reinsurer said on Friday, a business that analysts value at around 3.5 billion pounds  ($4.45 billion).

title: Bank of Japan's aggressive easing has created a tough environment for some banks: MUFG
text: The BOJ's negative interest rate policy has given many financial firms a tough time, according to Mitsubishi UFJ Financial Group's Nobuyuki Hirano.

title: The global boom in natural gas demand is about to slow, the International Energy Agency says
text: Gas demand grew at the fastest pace since 2010 last year, but a slowing global economy and other factors will put the brakes on growth.

title: 'World war for the client': Top banking execs say tech is the way to win
text: "We are in the world war for the client," says Jose Vinals, group chairman of Standard Chartered.

title: BlackRock says a US-China trade deal is likely this year â€” but markets won't be cheering
text: Even if the U.S. and China manage to resolve their conflict, investor sentiment will still be weighed down, says BlackRock's Isabelle Mateos y Lago.

title: Bills, Beige, And The Consequences Of The Disappeared Labor Shortage
text: The Bureau of Labor Statistics reported last month that the unemployment rate in the United States had fallen to just 3.6%.

title: Asia shares up on policy easing hopes, yuan slips on PBOC signals
text: Asian shares were slightly higher on Friday on expectations global central banks will soon embark on an easing cycle in the face of international trade frictions and fears of a world recession.

title: Germany's Opel town shows struggle for Europe to plug in electric cars
text: Carmakers and policymakers in Europe are staking their futures on a race to electric vehicles. But the vast charging network needed to sustain their vision is patchy, and it's not clear who'll pay for it.

title: Bearish Sentiment Still On The Rise
text: Despite the rally over the past two sessions, declines Monday and at the end of last week have dragged bullish sentiment from 24.8% last week down to 22.53%.

title: European markets set for solid gains as US jobs report looms
text: European stocks are expected to start Friday's session on a relatively positive note.
